Mockito Methods list: 
1. Creating Mocks

MyService mockService = mock(MyService.class);
Creates a mock object of the specified class/interface.



Mockito Methods list: 

2. Stubbing Method Calls

1. when(...).thenReturn(...)
when(mockService.getName()).thenReturn("Alice");
Specifies that when getName() is called, "Alice" should be returned.

2. when(...).thenThrow(...)
when(mockService.getData()).thenThrow(new RuntimeException("Error"));
Throws an exception when the method is called.

3. doReturn(...).when(...)
Used for stubbing void methods or avoiding early evaluation:
doReturn("Mocked").when(mockService).getName();


3. Stubbing Void Methods

1. doNothing().when(...)
doNothing().when(mockService).deleteUser(anyInt());
2. doThrow(...).when(...)
doThrow(new RuntimeException("Delete error")).when(mockService).deleteUser(anyInt());


4. Argument Matchers

Used to match parameters dynamically.
when(mockService.findUserById(anyInt())).thenReturn(new User(1, "Test"));
when(mockService.saveUser(any(User.class))).thenReturn(true);
Common matchers:
any(), anyInt(), anyString(), eq(value), isNull(), notNull()


5. Verifying Interactions

1. verify(...)
verify(mockService).getName();
Checks that the method was called.

2. verify(..., times(n))
verify(mockService, times(2)).getName();
Verifies the method was called exactly n times.

3. verifyNoMoreInteractions(...)
verifyNoMoreInteractions(mockService);
Fails if any other method was called on the mock.

4. verifyZeroInteractions(...) (deprecated, use verifyNoInteractions)
verifyNoInteractions(mockService);


6. Spying on Real Objects

Say,
List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
List<String> spyList = spy(list);

You can stub/verify like this:
doReturn(100).when(spyList).size();
verify(spyList).add("item");



7. Capturing Arguments

Use ArgumentCaptor to capture values passed to mocks:
ArgumentCaptor<String> captor = ArgumentCaptor.forClass(String.class);
verify(mockService).saveData(captor.capture());
System.out.println(captor.getValue());  // prints the argument


8. Resetting Mocks

reset(mockService);
Clears all interactions and stubs.


9. Timeout Verification (for async)

verify(mockService, timeout(100)).loadData();






